📜 Cursor Project Rules for Mightyfull Shop

📁 Project Structure
	•	Use a modular folder structure (components, hooks, lib, store, styles, utils, app).
	•	Keep all Shopify API-related logic inside lib/shopify

📦 Dependencies & Packages
	•	Use ShadCN for UI components.
	•	Use Tailwind CSS with tailwind-merge for class management.
	•	Use Radix UI for accessibility and interactive components.
	•	Use Embla Carousel for sliders and auto-scrolling behavior.
	•	Use GSAP & Lenis for smooth animations and scrolling.
	•	Use Zustand for state management.
	•	Use React Query for API calls and caching.

🖼️ Styling & Theming
	•	Prefer SCSS modules (.module.scss) for component-specific styles.
	•	Use Tailwind for global styles and utility-based design.
	•	Avoid inline styles unless necessary.

🚀 Next.js Best Practices
	•	Use Server Components (use client only when necessary).
	•	Enable Static/Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR) where applicable.
	•	Prefer React Suspense & Streaming for better performance.

🔄 State Management
	•	Use Zustand for global state (store/useCart.ts, store/useUser.ts).
	•	Keep minimal state in context; prefer local component state where possible.
	•	Use React Query (useQuery, useMutation) for async data fetching.

⚡ Performance & Optimization
	•	Use React Profiler for performance debugging.
	•	Avoid unnecessary re-renders with useMemo, useCallback.

🔍 Linting & Formatting
	•	Use ESLint with eslint-config-next.
	•	Use Prettier + @trivago/prettier-plugin-sort-imports for import sorting.
	•	Follow a strict TypeScript convention (@types/node, @types/react).


